This paper discusses a new in-memory query processing engine that uses worst-case optimal joins as its core execution mechanism for both business intelligence (BI) and linear algebra (LA) queries. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the following sub-categories: 

- cs.DB (Databases): The paper focuses on unifying BI and LA workloads in a single framework, which is a common problem in the database community. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper proposes a new query processing architecture that uses worst-case optimal joins, which is a topic of interest in the algorithms community. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper mentions that pipelines combining SQL-style BI queries and LA are becoming increasingly common in industry, which suggests that machine learning techniques may be involved. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): Similar to the previous point, the use of BI and LA pipelines in industry may involve artificial intelligence techniques. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper presents a new in-memory query processing engine called LevelHeaded, which is a software engineering topic.
